    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I guess this is because `foo()`'s scope is tied to its outer scope (globally, in this case) and since `bar()` is in this outer scope, `foo()` is visible inside `bar()`'s body. However, the scope of `x` is tied to `foo()`'s scope which does not cross function boundary.",
